-- Greenberg Says China Leaders Amenable to Trade Deal With U.S.
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-04-03T12:22:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/greenberg-says-china-leaders-amenable-to-trade-deal-with-u-s-.html
Maurice “Hank” Greenberg, the
former chairman and chief executive officer of  American
International Group Inc. (AIG) , said leaders in  China  would be open to
a free trade agreement with the U.S.  “They are amenable to it,” Greenberg told Bloomberg
Television’s Betty Liu on the “In the Loop” program today,
after returning from a visit to China where he met with
government and business leaders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  